1 
00:00:00,465 --> 00:00:02,426
Whoa, that's awesome!

2
00:00:02,509 --> 00:00:04,678
Poirot really made it into the magazine!

3
00:00:04,761 --> 00:00:05,846
That's right.

4
00:00:06,138 --> 00:00:10,183
A reporter came by the other day and
said we'd be in a book,

5
00:00:10,726 --> 00:00:14,438
but I never imagined we'd get
such a big feature.

6
00:00:14,521 --> 00:00:16,523
You're in it too, Azusa-san.

7
00:00:16,607 --> 00:00:17,899
Look, right here.

8
00:00:17,983 --> 00:00:21,570
"With this shop's regular customer,
the calico cat Taii-kun..."

9
00:00:21,653 --> 00:00:23,572
"and the beautiful waitress Azusa-san."

10
00:00:24,031 --> 00:00:26,700
It's true! She's holding Dai-chan.

11
00:00:26,908 --> 00:00:29,995
Oh come on, "beautiful"
is laying it on too thick.

12
00:00:30,537 --> 00:00:33,498
These things tend to be written
a bit over the top.

13
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:36,084
R-Right.

14
00:00:36,501 --> 00:00:39,421
How come Amuro-niichan isn't in it?

15
00:00:39,504 --> 00:00:43,508
Ah, I happened to be off sick that day.

16
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,136
That's a real shame.

17
00:00:46,219 --> 00:00:47,888
And you're so handsome too.

18
00:00:48,263 --> 00:00:51,975
Well, a man dressed all in black
wouldn't go showing his face...

19
00:00:52,059 --> 00:00:54,603
in some lightweight gourmet
magazine, now would he?

20
00:00:55,145 --> 00:00:58,649
More importantly, weren't there
one more of you kids?

21
00:00:58,732 --> 00:01:00,567
Ai-chan already went home.

22
00:01:00,901 --> 00:01:03,612
We invited her to come to Poirot
with us to see the cat,

23
00:01:03,695 --> 00:01:05,155
but she said...

24
00:01:05,238 --> 00:01:07,574
that she suddenly remembered
she had something to do.

25
00:01:07,658 --> 00:01:10,744
N-Now that you mention it,
where's the cat?

26
00:01:10,827 --> 00:01:13,038
Did he already come by
for his food?

27
00:01:13,121 --> 00:01:14,706
No, actually...

28
00:01:15,499 --> 00:01:20,629
Since last week, Taii-kun has
become my house cat.

29
00:01:20,962 --> 00:01:22,047
Huh?

30
00:01:22,130 --> 00:01:24,466
Are you sure that's okay?

31
00:01:24,549 --> 00:01:27,844
Taii is a stray, but he was
wearing a collar,

32
00:01:27,928 --> 00:01:30,138
so wasn't he someone's
pet originally?

33
00:01:30,514 --> 00:01:35,227
Well, the other day he got into
a fight with a neighborhood cat,

34
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:38,897
and showed up covered in wounds,
so I got worried.

35
00:01:39,189 --> 00:01:41,942
And besides, his photo
ended up in the magazine.

36
00:01:42,025 --> 00:01:44,569
If his owner is really
looking for him...

37
00:01:45,237 --> 00:01:47,906
I figured they'd see the article
and come forward.

38
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:51,952
But still, Dai-chan, keeping him all
to yourself isn't fair!

39
00:01:52,202 --> 00:01:57,374
Besides, there's no way an owner would
turn up from such a tiny photo.

40
00:01:57,457 --> 00:01:59,793
Unless it was going around online,
that'd be different.

41
00:02:00,669 --> 00:02:01,837
That's what you'd think, right?

42
00:02:02,045 --> 00:02:03,588
But guess what...

43
00:02:03,672 --> 00:02:05,340
- Excuse me.
- Hm?

44
00:02:05,799 --> 00:02:08,593
Is this the place from the magazine,
the shop called Poirot?

45
00:02:08,677 --> 00:02:09,970
Oh, yes.

46
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:12,723
It said in the article, right?

47
00:02:12,806 --> 00:02:14,933
That come evening, there's a stray
cat that shows up...

48
00:02:15,142 --> 00:02:16,476
begging for food.

49
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:18,603
- With a photo and all.
- Yes.

50
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,857
Truth is, that's my cat.
- Shogo Amezawa (36), Freeter.

51
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:24,484
I've been searching for him
for about half a year.

52
00:02:24,818 --> 00:02:26,361
- Huh?
- H-Hey.

53
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:28,697
What are you talking about?

54
00:02:28,989 --> 00:02:32,117
That's without a doubt my house cat.
- Teishi Masuko (56), company president.

55
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,952
Don't go spouting nonsense.

56
00:02:34,369 --> 00:02:35,454
Huh?

57
00:02:35,746 --> 00:02:39,416
Amazing! An owner actually
showed up!

58
00:02:39,499 --> 00:02:41,543
A-And two of them, no less!

59
00:02:41,710 --> 00:02:44,504
A-Actually, it's not two.

60
00:02:44,588 --> 00:02:47,549
There's one more person inside the shop right now.

61
00:02:47,799 --> 00:02:48,800
Huh?

62
00:02:51,970 --> 00:02:53,722
A refreshing autumn breeze blows through

63
00:02:53,805 --> 00:02:55,515
The gaiety of summer for a stylish and dashing display of deduction.

64
00:02:55,599 --> 00:02:59,019
Three owners came forward?
Kogoro and Bourbon, a deduction tag-team.

65
00:02:59,102 --> 00:03:00,520
Seeing through to the
one and only truth.

66
00:03:00,604 --> 00:03:02,481
Looks like a kid, mind of an adult.

67
00:03:02,564 --> 00:03:05,317
His name is Detective Conan!

68
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:13,235
♪~

69
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:47,245
~♪

70
00:04:49,194 --> 00:04:54,394
"Lucky Calico Cat Case (Part 1)"

71
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:58,048
Honestly, don't make me say it over and over.

72
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,717
This cat belongs to my granddaughter,
- Mutsumi Shagawa (61), housewife.

73
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,552
her pet cat, Mugi-chan.

74
00:05:03,178 --> 00:05:04,804
Where's Mugi-chan?

75
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:07,223
Weren't you going to bring her here?

76
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,391
O-Oh, yes.

77
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:11,478
I stepped outside to go fetch her,

78
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:14,397
but while I was talking
with these children...

79
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:18,693
these people showed up saying
they were the owners.

80
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:22,030
No, the real owner is me...

81
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:24,699
Wrong! I keep telling you, it's me!

82
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:28,661
Are you people trying to steal
my granddaughter's cat?

83
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,331
Amazing! Dai-chan's super popular.

84
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:33,208
But why all three of them?

85
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:36,544
He's just an ordinary calico cat
you'd find anywhere.

86
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:38,922
That's the thing, he isn't
ordinary.

87
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:40,507
Huh?

88
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:43,301
He's certainly a clever cat,
I'll give you that.

89
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:47,472
When he got trapped in that
shady delivery truck,

90
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:51,226
he delivered Conan-kun's
message here, after all.

91
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:54,396
Dai-chan really saved the day
back then.

92
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:59,192
But even though he delivered it,
the wind blew it away, right?

93
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:00,985
Y-Yeah.

94
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:03,947
Anyways Azusa-san, head back home...

95
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:06,282
- and bring Taii here.
- O-Okay.

96
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:12,080
While we wait, let's hear out
these three individually.

97
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:16,084
- With a mystery-solving expert joining us.
- Huh?

98
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:20,797
A mystery-solving expert... don't tell me...

99
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:24,259
What? Searching for a cat's owner?

100
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:28,179
Do that somewhere else. I'm busy right now.

101
00:06:28,263 --> 00:06:29,264
Honestly...

102
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,015
(cat meows)

103
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:33,768
- Goro-chan?
- Why's it here?

104
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:36,938
Isn't this that scary lady's cat?

105
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:39,482
"Scary lady"...

106
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,360
Mom's away in Fukuoka for work,

107
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:45,697
so she told me to look after him 
just for tonight.

108
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:46,781
Huh.

109
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,491
Go home, go home.

110
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:52,162
It's not like anyone's going
to pay me a fee, right?

111
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:54,122
Then I'll hire you.

112
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:57,625
For the fee, premier seat tickets to...

113
00:06:57,709 --> 00:06:59,544
Yoko Okino's summer live concert.

114
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:00,628
What?!

115
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:04,632
Now then, the first owner is...

116
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:08,344
- Shagawa-san, you're a housewife?
- Yes.

117
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:11,347
This old man is really easy to win over.

118
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:15,268
So, when did the cat disappear?

119
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:17,145
About two months ago.

120
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:21,149
We were going on a family trip,
so we left him with an acquaintance,

121
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:25,153
but the moment they took their eyes
off him, he apparently vanished.

122
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:29,532
This is a photo of the cat's owner,
my granddaughter.

123
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:32,118
It was taken five years ago.

124
00:07:32,202 --> 00:07:35,038
I see. He's still a kitten here,

125
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:39,334
but the pattern of the markings
does look similar.

126
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:42,170
Right? You think so too,
don't you, detective?

127
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:43,671
Sure.

128
00:07:43,755 --> 00:07:46,216
So, do you like cats too, ma'am?

129
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:48,593
Yes, of course.

130
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:51,054
Come here, come here.

131
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,222
Come on.

132
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:54,807
(cat meows)

133
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:58,478
My, what a shy cat.

134
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:00,688
He seems to really like you, sir.

135
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:02,941
He's not my cat, though.

136
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:07,737
The calico in question had marks
from a neutering surgery.

137
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:11,032
Ah, that was such an ordeal.

138
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:13,785
He stayed overnight at the clinic
and came back,

139
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,954
but the bandages just wouldn't come off.

140
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:20,500
It took about a week before
the stitches came out.

141
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,920
Masuko-san, IT company president.

142
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:28,424
You'd be the second candidate owner,

143
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:30,718
so when did the cat go missing?

144
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:34,222
Exactly four months ago, during my move.

145
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:38,309
My wife of 30 years passed away,

146
00:08:38,393 --> 00:08:42,313
so I decided to sell the house
and move into a condominium.

147
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:46,818
I'm sure I put him in a carrier and
loaded him onto the moving truck,

148
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:48,319
but when it was time to unload...

149
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:50,613
- he was gone from the carrier.
- Hoh.

150
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:53,157
Do you have a photo or anything?

151
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,618
I have one I took on my phone.

152
00:08:56,119 --> 00:09:00,373
The one with the cat is my wife.
I took the picture.

153
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:05,253
Well now, this is the spitting
image of Poirot's cat.

154
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:06,879
Of course it is.

155
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:08,590
Because it's the same cat.

156
00:09:08,923 --> 00:09:11,009
So, do you like cats too, mister?

157
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:13,177
- Yeah.
- Want to try holding him?

158
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:15,138
(sneezes)

159
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,807
Hm? Do you have a cold?

160
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:20,393
A-Ah, m-maybe so.

161
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:23,855
By the way, did your cat get neutered?

162
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:29,360
Yes, but I left that sort of thing
to my wife, so I'm not sure of the details.

163
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:33,448
But I do remember that even after
the surgery, he didn't wear bandages.

164
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:35,867
For some reason he had something
like a satellite dish...

165
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,786
attached around his neck.
That much I recall.

166
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:42,040
Like I said, if you'd just
let me meet the cat...

167
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:44,292
I'd know right away,
that's what I'm telling you.

168
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:46,711
That I'm the owner.

169
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:49,631
Well, let me hear you out first.

170
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:51,049
Amesawa-san, the freelancer.

171
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,635
When did he go missing?

172
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:55,386
About half a year ago.

173
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:59,474
I love freedom, so I let
my cat roam free too.

174
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:02,685
Then one day, he just
stopped coming home.

175
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:04,562
Do you have any photos?

176
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:08,566
No way I'd take any,
when I let him roam free.

177
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,402
So, you like cats too, right, mister?

178
00:10:11,486 --> 00:10:12,904
Yeah, naturally.

179
00:10:15,156 --> 00:10:18,451
- Come here.
- (cat meows)

180
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:22,747
No way! Goro's actually
pretty shy around people.

181
00:10:23,247 --> 00:10:26,668
Guess I've just got the kind of
body animals take a liking to.

182
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:30,338
So, do you remember the cat
getting neutered?

183
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:32,465
Well, I got him after he'd already...

184
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:35,301
gotten pretty big, so I'm not sure.

185
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,262
By the way, about that calico cat...

186
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:41,391
he was written up as "Taii-kun,"
but it's a female cat.

187
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:45,395
Huh? A-Ah, well, in that case
maybe it's not mine.

188
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,606
- What are you saying?
- Taii's a male!

189
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:51,818
- He had a pair down there!
- Oh, was that right?

190
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:56,072
D-Don't scare me like that.
Of course it's a male.

191
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:58,074
(cat meows)

192
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,076
Hmm...

193
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:04,831
So in the end, which of those
three was the owner?

194
00:11:04,914 --> 00:11:06,791
Gotta be that guy, right?

195
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,293
Goro was super attached to him too.

196
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:13,798
But the photo on the mister's phone
looked exactly like Taii.

197
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:17,593
Yeah, but he himself wasn't in the photo.

198
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:20,972
Then what about the photo the lady showed us?

199
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:24,600
But that was a photo from
when he was a kitten.

200
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:27,687
Conan-kun, did you come up with something?

201
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:28,813
Not quite yet.

202
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:31,816
- (horse racing broadcast)
- Hm? There it is, go!

203
00:11:31,899 --> 00:11:34,861
Turn the volume down!
We're all trying to think here.

204
00:11:35,153 --> 00:11:36,320
Sound?

205
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,241
That's right! Let's tell Ai-chan too.

206
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:44,245
Huh, three owners for Dai-chan.

207
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,539
So, how's it going?

208
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:48,416
Everyone's stumped.

209
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,752
Wondering who the owner is.

210
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:53,963
- Not everyone, I mean Edogawa-kun.
- Huh?

211
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:55,339
What kind of face is he making?

212
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:56,799
Um...

213
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:02,305
He's grinning, with this
mischievous look on his face.

214
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:04,307
Then it's fine.

215
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:06,976
Looks like he's found the owner.

216
00:12:16,950 --> 00:12:19,703
Hey, hey, what's the meaning of this?

217
00:12:19,953 --> 00:12:24,207
Didn't you gather us here because
you figured out who the owner is?

218
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:28,128
That's why Azusa-chan from Poirot
will be here soon...

219
00:12:28,211 --> 00:12:30,047
bringing that calico cat.

220
00:12:30,672 --> 00:12:33,592
What? Then you should've said so sooner.

221
00:12:33,675 --> 00:12:36,553
Once we meet him, we'll know who the owner is.

222
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:40,891
But in my case, it's my
granddaughter who's the owner.

223
00:12:41,391 --> 00:12:43,226
- Sorry for the wait.
- (cat meows)

224
00:12:43,477 --> 00:12:44,478
Dai-chan!

225
00:12:45,187 --> 00:12:48,940
(meowing)

226
00:12:50,525 --> 00:12:53,195
See that? He's my cat after all!

227
00:12:54,237 --> 00:12:57,157
Now then, I'll be taking
this cat home with me.

228
00:12:57,657 --> 00:13:01,078
But you know, when a cat sees
three people standing together,

229
00:13:01,161 --> 00:13:03,914
it has a habit of being drawn
to the person in the middle.

230
00:13:03,997 --> 00:13:06,333
So maybe he just jumped at you
because you happened to be...

231
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:08,210
standing in the middle, mister.

232
00:13:08,543 --> 00:13:11,129
- What?
- Is that true, Conan-kun?

233
00:13:11,213 --> 00:13:13,715
Yeah, they showed it on TV the other day.

234
00:13:13,924 --> 00:13:15,759
That must be exactly it.

235
00:13:15,842 --> 00:13:18,720
Otherwise, our cat wouldn't go to
a shady man like this.

236
00:13:19,096 --> 00:13:21,264
Then let's try it again.

237
00:13:21,348 --> 00:13:24,101
I don't care whether I'm on
the right or left.

238
00:13:24,434 --> 00:13:27,646
Actually, there's an even
clearer way to do this.

239
00:13:27,729 --> 00:13:30,607
An experiment that'll tell us
the owner in one shot.

240
00:13:31,441 --> 00:13:33,610
Azusa-san, are you ready?

241
00:13:33,902 --> 00:13:38,990
Yeah. Taii-kun is eating his food
quietly in front of the office door.

242
00:13:39,825 --> 00:13:43,078
Okay, one at a time, approach
the door and open it.

243
00:13:43,161 --> 00:13:44,246
If it's one-on-one...

244
00:13:44,329 --> 00:13:46,957
the cat should be able to tell
if you're his owner or not.

245
00:13:47,499 --> 00:13:49,000
First up, Shagawa-san.

246
00:13:49,501 --> 00:13:51,211
O-Okay.

247
00:13:59,594 --> 00:14:03,640
Come on, Mugi-chan, it's me.
Don't you recognize me?

248
00:14:05,142 --> 00:14:06,560
Mugi-chan.

249
00:14:07,102 --> 00:14:11,314
I-I guess it really has to be
the owner's granddaughter.

250
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,484
No, it'd be the same even with
your granddaughter.

251
00:14:15,235 --> 00:14:19,865
Because the cat you're looking for,
unlike this one, is female.

252
00:14:20,073 --> 00:14:22,576
- Wha...
- Isn't that right?

253
00:14:22,659 --> 00:14:24,369
Amuro-niichan.

254
00:14:24,828 --> 00:14:27,497
Right. Shagawa-san, you said it yourself,

255
00:14:28,081 --> 00:14:30,625
that for the neutering surgery,
the cat stayed overnight,

256
00:14:30,709 --> 00:14:33,253
and it took a week before
the stitches came out.

257
00:14:33,336 --> 00:14:34,463
Y-Yes.

258
00:14:34,546 --> 00:14:39,342
That isn't a male neutering, that's
a female spaying procedure.

259
00:14:39,926 --> 00:14:45,474
Spaying is a major operation that opens
the abdomen to remove the ovaries,

260
00:14:45,557 --> 00:14:48,226
but neutering only involves making
a small cut in the scrotum...

261
00:14:48,310 --> 00:14:52,397
and removing the testes. It's a simple
procedure, so it's done same-day as a rule.

262
00:14:52,898 --> 00:14:55,775
And as Masuko-san said,

263
00:14:55,859 --> 00:14:57,736
to keep the cat from licking
the wound,

264
00:14:57,819 --> 00:15:00,530
all that's needed is a collar
around the neck.

265
00:15:00,947 --> 00:15:02,365
And besides, ma'am,

266
00:15:02,449 --> 00:15:06,036
you talked as if you kept the cat
together with your granddaughter,

267
00:15:06,578 --> 00:15:10,165
but the truth is, your granddaughter
only brought him over once in a while, right?

268
00:15:10,665 --> 00:15:13,376
Because you're not used to
handling cats.

269
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:18,131
Owner aside, cats dislike
being stared at.

270
00:15:18,298 --> 00:15:21,927
That's why, back then, rather than going
to you, ma'am, who kept calling him over,

271
00:15:22,010 --> 00:15:23,386
he went to someone
with no interest...

272
00:15:23,470 --> 00:15:26,181
in cats, Kogoro-ojisan.

273
00:15:26,681 --> 00:15:30,560
Probably your granddaughter had
something she had to leave home for,

274
00:15:30,852 --> 00:15:35,440
and asked you to look after the cat,
but he wandered off somewhere, didn't he?

275
00:15:35,941 --> 00:15:37,651
You're exactly right, boy.

276
00:15:37,734 --> 00:15:40,320
My granddaughter is on a school trip,

277
00:15:40,403 --> 00:15:43,448
and her parents took the chance
to go abroad.

278
00:15:43,615 --> 00:15:46,785
I was asked to look after the cat,

279
00:15:46,868 --> 00:15:49,704
but he just wouldn't warm
up to me.

280
00:15:49,913 --> 00:15:54,209
The moment I took my eyes off him,
he was nowhere to be seen.

281
00:15:54,584 --> 00:15:57,003
I was at a complete loss for what to do,

282
00:15:57,087 --> 00:16:00,924
when that magazine photo of
the cat caught my eye.

283
00:16:01,258 --> 00:16:05,428
So in place of the cat that vanished,
you went for Poirot's cat.

284
00:16:05,512 --> 00:16:09,724
But a male and a female would
differ in build and such.

285
00:16:10,016 --> 00:16:15,230
B-But my granddaughter comes back
from her school trip tonight.

286
00:16:15,313 --> 00:16:19,359
If I don't sort it out by then, I won't
be able to face my granddaughter.

287
00:16:19,693 --> 00:16:24,364
- When did he go missing?
- After he ate last night.

288
00:16:24,656 --> 00:16:28,743
I searched everywhere a cat might
slip into, gaps in furniture,

289
00:16:28,827 --> 00:16:32,247
any place a door was open,
but he was nowhere.

290
00:16:32,914 --> 00:16:36,501
Then try looking in places
where doors are closed.

291
00:16:36,585 --> 00:16:39,921
The bathroom, inside the washing
machine, the closet.

292
00:16:40,005 --> 00:16:44,926
Cats sometimes slip right inside the
moment a person opens a door.

293
00:16:45,218 --> 00:16:48,138
I-I'll go look one more time.

294
00:16:49,514 --> 00:16:52,642
Sheesh, what an outrageous old lady.

295
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:58,565
Okay, next, Amesawa-san, you try it,
just like Shagawa-san did.

296
00:16:59,065 --> 00:17:01,151
Sure, bring it on.

297
00:17:01,234 --> 00:17:04,904
Though the result's obvious
before I even start.

298
00:17:04,988 --> 00:17:06,239
That's right, Conan-kun.

299
00:17:06,573 --> 00:17:08,199
He'll just leap at him. like before...

300
00:17:08,283 --> 00:17:11,494
and start purring, won't he?

301
00:17:12,370 --> 00:17:13,622
Heh. Hm?

302
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:18,668
H-Hey, what's the matter?

303
00:17:18,752 --> 00:17:20,295
Come to me like before.

304
00:17:20,629 --> 00:17:22,047
I said come here.

305
00:17:22,213 --> 00:17:23,381
- (cat meows)
- Ah!

306
00:17:23,882 --> 00:17:25,884
- Don't you know?
- Huh?

307
00:17:26,551 --> 00:17:29,846
Catnip only works for about
five to ten minutes.

308
00:17:29,929 --> 00:17:33,475
Once that passes, to the cat
you're just some...

309
00:17:33,558 --> 00:17:36,186
scary guy who yells in a loud voice.

310
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:40,690
The proof is that Goro, who was
clinging to you at first,

311
00:17:41,066 --> 00:17:43,818
is now scared and won't even go near you.

312
00:17:43,902 --> 00:17:47,530
- A-Ah...
- Well, a real owner wouldn't...

313
00:17:47,614 --> 00:17:50,325
come to pick up his cat by
dusting catnip powder...

314
00:17:50,408 --> 00:17:52,452
all over his own body, now would he?

315
00:17:52,702 --> 00:17:54,996
A-Ah, no, this is, um...

316
00:17:55,413 --> 00:17:59,542
Besides, when Conan-kun told you
the cat was female,

317
00:17:59,626 --> 00:18:01,961
you tried to back off right away.

318
00:18:02,045 --> 00:18:04,005
- Huh?
- If you'd seen the magazine photo,

319
00:18:04,089 --> 00:18:05,965
become certain it was your cat,

320
00:18:06,341 --> 00:18:10,220
and gone out of your way to come get him,
you'd have pressed harder.

321
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,055
You knew, didn't you?

322
00:18:12,138 --> 00:18:15,767
That if the cat were female,
it'd have no value.

323
00:18:16,726 --> 00:18:19,396
Value? It's just a mutt, isn't it?

324
00:18:19,562 --> 00:18:21,690
A female calico, sure.

325
00:18:22,399 --> 00:18:27,195
But due to a chromosomal anomaly, males are
born at a rate of only one in a thousand,

326
00:18:27,278 --> 00:18:31,533
and because of that rarity, they're said to be
the model for the so-called "lucky cat."

327
00:18:31,616 --> 00:18:33,326
At least one million yen,

328
00:18:33,410 --> 00:18:36,579
and I've heard they've even gone
for as much as 20 million yen.

329
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:39,416
- T-Twenty million yen?
- No way!

330
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,084
Amazing, Dai-chan!

331
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:43,128
On par with a white lion!

332
00:18:43,211 --> 00:18:46,881
W-With that much, that's,
um, how many eel bowls...

333
00:18:47,298 --> 00:18:50,176
You clearly knew its value,

334
00:18:50,260 --> 00:18:53,471
so there's no way you'd let it roam
free in this city, is there?

335
00:18:53,555 --> 00:18:55,432
I-I...

336
00:18:55,974 --> 00:18:59,519
Excuse me!

337
00:19:01,688 --> 00:19:03,982
Now then, lastly,
Masuko-san, you try.

338
00:19:04,065 --> 00:19:05,692
A-Ah.

339
00:19:06,317 --> 00:19:09,654
But I haven't seen him in four months,

340
00:19:09,738 --> 00:19:12,741
and it was mostly my wife who fed him.

341
00:19:14,117 --> 00:19:17,704
I might get the same result
as those other two.

342
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:19,956
Ah...

343
00:19:21,249 --> 00:19:24,461
- S-Soseki.
- (cat meows)

344
00:19:25,295 --> 00:19:28,339
You remembered me, didn't you, Soseki?

345
00:19:28,423 --> 00:19:29,716
(cat meows)

346
00:19:30,425 --> 00:19:31,676
But why?

347
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:35,180
It was almost as if he was waiting
in front of the door before it opened...

348
00:19:35,263 --> 00:19:36,306
It's the sound.

349
00:19:36,389 --> 00:19:40,310
Cats have incredibly good ears,
and they remember their...

350
00:19:40,393 --> 00:19:43,480
owner's footsteps perfectly.
They showed it on TV.

351
00:19:44,272 --> 00:19:45,857
Hey, you said the cat went missing...

352
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:47,984
during your move, right?

353
00:19:48,526 --> 00:19:52,447
Did you happen to use
Cheetah Moving Center?

354
00:19:52,655 --> 00:19:55,492
A-Ah, yes. But how did you
know that?

355
00:19:55,867 --> 00:19:58,328
Because that cat once climbed
into a delivery truck...

356
00:19:58,411 --> 00:20:02,457
container from the same company before.

357
00:20:02,874 --> 00:20:04,793
I see, so that was...

358
00:20:05,126 --> 00:20:08,004
He wanted to get back to his owner.

359
00:20:08,338 --> 00:20:11,925
He thought he could go home if
he got on a truck with the same logo.

360
00:20:12,383 --> 00:20:14,469
Good for you, Dai-chan.

361
00:20:14,844 --> 00:20:18,515
(cat meows and sneezes)

362
00:20:20,225 --> 00:20:23,019
Well then, thank you all for everything.

363
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:25,772
Bye-bye, Dai-chan.

364
00:20:25,855 --> 00:20:29,025
- Take care.
- Don't run off again, okay?

365
00:20:29,692 --> 00:20:31,027
Haha. Hm?

366
00:20:34,656 --> 00:20:37,867
This is my address and email.

367
00:20:37,951 --> 00:20:39,994
If it works out, come visit him.

368
00:20:40,453 --> 00:20:42,288
Really? Thank you!

369
00:20:43,623 --> 00:20:45,792
(sneezes)

370
00:20:46,584 --> 00:20:48,378
But I had no idea.

371
00:20:48,461 --> 00:20:50,922
That cats are drawn to the
person in the middle.

372
00:20:51,005 --> 00:20:53,216
Ah, that was a lie.

373
00:20:53,299 --> 00:20:55,343
- Huh?
- If I hadn't said something like that,

374
00:20:55,426 --> 00:20:58,388
we wouldn't have been able to
do that footstep experiment.

375
00:20:58,471 --> 00:21:00,056
You set up a fake, didn't you?

376
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:04,060
With that innocent smile,
playing it coy like a cat.

377
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:05,311
Huh?

378
00:21:05,854 --> 00:21:09,315
- Ah, you know, fitting for a cat case.
- A pun, really?

379
00:21:13,903 --> 00:21:19,909
♪~

380
00:22:27,810 --> 00:22:33,316
~♪

381
00:22:34,192 --> 00:22:35,735
But still, from that mister...

382
00:22:35,818 --> 00:22:38,196
I never thought we'd hear from him.

383
00:22:38,696 --> 00:22:41,157
"If you want to see the cat,
come today."

384
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:44,118
An email came to the detective
agency, right?

385
00:22:44,202 --> 00:22:45,870
- Yeah.
- It hasn't even been...

386
00:22:45,954 --> 00:22:48,373
- that many days since then.
- I wonder why?

387
00:22:48,873 --> 00:22:51,751
Maybe he decided to let
him go after all?

388
00:22:51,834 --> 00:22:54,170
That guy seemed to have a cat allergy.

389
00:22:54,462 --> 00:22:56,506
A c-cat allergy?

390
00:22:56,589 --> 00:22:58,675
And yet he was keeping a cat?

391
00:22:59,008 --> 00:23:00,385
(elevator arrival chime)

392
00:23:00,468 --> 00:23:03,346
Well, sometimes people keep cats
without knowing they're allergic,

393
00:23:03,429 --> 00:23:06,182
and sometimes they develop
the allergy while keeping one.

394
00:23:06,391 --> 00:23:09,727
But still, in that case, is he
going to sell him after all?

395
00:23:09,978 --> 00:23:13,022
- Huh?
- It's 20 million yen, after all.

396
00:23:13,106 --> 00:23:15,984
This is the room, right?
Masuko-san's place.

397
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:18,069
Just open the door,
please!

398
00:23:18,152 --> 00:23:19,737
There was a strange sound!

399
00:23:23,616 --> 00:23:27,578
Masuko-san, it's the building
manager. Are you all right?

400
00:23:28,162 --> 00:23:30,039
- Hm?
- (cat meows)

401
00:23:30,123 --> 00:23:32,166
Huh? What's with this cat?

402
00:23:32,458 --> 00:23:34,377
Mister, is something wrong?

403
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:36,546
- Hm?
- Ah, no, this cat...

404
00:23:36,629 --> 00:23:39,841
It doesn't seem to be hurt,
but there's blood on its paws.

405
00:23:40,466 --> 00:23:42,844
Which means... don't tell me,
Masuko-san...

406
00:23:44,595 --> 00:23:45,680
Don't tell me...

407
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:53,104
There's blood on its paws.

408
00:23:53,521 --> 00:23:54,981
Something happened inside.

409
00:23:55,398 --> 00:23:56,399
You guys.

410
00:23:56,482 --> 00:23:58,443
- Do you have any string?
- Huh?

411
00:23:59,027 --> 00:24:00,361
The back room, huh.

412
00:24:02,989 --> 00:24:04,907
This is no time for you two
to be flirting...

413
00:24:04,991 --> 00:24:06,409
- with each other.
- Wha...

414
00:24:07,201 --> 00:24:08,953
There's tape and scissors, and yet...

415
00:24:09,704 --> 00:24:11,456
The trash can nearby is empty too.

416
00:24:12,373 --> 00:24:14,834
Why isn't it here? That thing.

417
00:24:15,328 --> 00:24:16,728
Next Conan,

418
00:24:16,728 --> 00:24:21,028
"Lucky Calico Cat Case (Part 2)".

419
00:24:36,528 --> 00:24:38,628
Next Conan's Hint:

420
00:24:38,628 --> 00:24:41,028
"Wrapping".

421
00:24:41,130 --> 00:24:43,299
Next week is the second half!
Tune in, Yeah!

422
00:24:43,382 --> 00:24:45,760
- That's a rapper.
- It's suppose to be wrapping.
